<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

{{>header}}

<head>
    <title>Herds</title>
    <style>
        /* Edit these to adjust chord diagram parameters. */
        .group-label {
            font: 10px inherit;
        }

        .group-tick line {
            stroke: #000;
        }

        .ribbons {
            fill-opacity: 0.67;
        }

        .chord-svg {

        }

        div.panel-body :below-level {
            width: inherit;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

{{>navbar}}

<div class="container">
    <div class="page-header" id="dashboard-banner">
        <div class="row">

            <div class="col-md-10">
                <h1>Herds</h1>
                <p class="lead">See how they all move around.</p>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
    <div class="row">

        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="panel panel-default">

                <div class="panel-body">
                    <h5>Tribe Definitions</h5>

                    <div class="row">

                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="panel panel-default" style="min-height: 20em;">
                                <div class="panel-body">
                                    <h5>Customer Overlap</h5>
                                    <p>The distribution of DUSA customers can be shown by tracking individual user purchases at multiple locations.<br>
                                        Using this data, we can model the overlap between customers who use multiple DUSA venues each week, and plot the flow between said venues specifically.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="panel panel-default" style="min-height: 20em;">
                                <div class="panel-body">
                                    <h5>24 Hour View</h5>
                                    <p>By segmenting transactions by hour, we can view overall purchasing trends over the course of the day to identify when DUSA venues are at their busiest.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-md-4">
                            <div class="panel panel-default" style="min-height: 20em;">
                                <div class="panel-body">
                                    <h5>Nightlife</h5>
                                    <p>Showing transactions across the course of the evening can show the peak times for DUSA's nightlife using YOYO.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">

        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <div class="panel-body">

                <h5> Flow of YOYO Transactions</h5>

                    <div class="panel panel-info">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h3 class="panel-title"> <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-exclamation-sign"></span> Chord Diagram Use</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="panel-body">
                            You can interact with the chord diagrams below by hovering your mouse over the segments on the outside of the circle.<br>
                            Ribbons/paths show the flow of users between segments, with the end representing flow to a segment from the other. <br>
                            Customers are assigned to a venue based on where most of their transactions were recorded. <br>
                            The <b>Overlap</b> tab shows relative customer overlap between venues over the latest week on record. <br>
                            The <b>Flow</b> tab shows absolute customer movement between venues over the latest week on record.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                <ul class="nav nav-tabs">
                    <li class="active"><a data-toggle="tab" href="#view1">Overlap</a></li>
                    <li><a data-toggle="tab" href="#view2">Flow</a></li>
                </ul>

                <div class="panel-body">
                    <div class="tab-content" style="position: relative; width:80vw; margin:auto;">

                        <div id="view1" class="tab-pane fade in active">
                            <!-- OVERLAP TAB -->
                            <!-- <div id="OverlapText">
                                <p>This chord diagram shows the customer overlap between venues over the course of the last week.</p>
                            </div> -->

                            <div class="chord-svg-div" id="herds-chords-div">
                                <svg class="chord-svg" id="herds-chords"></svg>
                            </div>

                        </div>

                        <div id="view2" class="tab-pane fade">

                            <!-- <div id="FlowText">
                                <p>This chord diagram shows the exact flow of customers between venues over the course of the last week.</p>
                            </div> -->

                            <div class="chord-svg-div" id="herds-flows-div">
                                <svg class="chord-svg" id="herds-flows"></svg>
                            </div>

                            <script src="/js/herdsChord.min.js"></script>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="panel panel-default">

                <div class="panel-body">
                    <h5> Night vs Day</h5>

                    <div class="panel panel-info">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h3 class="panel-title"> <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-exclamation-sign"></span>Radar Plot Use</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="panel-body">
                            Filler text here.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <canvas id="nightVsDay" width="100" height="93"></canvas>
                    {{>nightVsDay}}
                    <br>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <h5>Nightlife (Transactions)</h5>
                    <p>Include graph representing 9pm-3am, thresholded by 15min increments?</p>
                    <canvas id="9to3graph" width="50" height="50"></canvas>
                    {{>9to3graph}}
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>
</body>

{{>footer}}